ExcelExample

Yu Bai

July 11, 2015

Demo on how to read formatted data from Excel into R via packages readxl and xlsx.

Read in an Excel file

library(readxl)

#first to see how many and what spreadsheets there are in the excel file
excel_sheets("examples.xls")
## [1] "experiment1"

#read in a given spreadsheet
wb_data <- read_excel("examples.xls",sheet=1, col_names=T, col_types=NULL, na="NA", skip=0)

class(wb_data) 
## [1] "tbl_df"     "tbl"        "data.frame"

head(wb_data)
##   variable ratio pvalue annotation
## 1       v1  0.51 0.0012          V
## 2       v2  0.54 0.0043          S
## 3       v3  0.16 0.0004         ER
## 4       v4  0.27 0.0001         MT
## 5       v5  0.96 0.0600       <NA>
## 6       v6  1.04 0.4800          C

Write to an (formatted) Excel file

library(xlsx)

##create an empty workbook object
outwb <- createWorkbook(type="xlsx")
outsheet <- createSheet(outwb, sheetName="myexperiment1")
      
## setup some basic styles
csColNames <- CellStyle(outwb) + Font(outwb, isBold=TRUE) + Alignment(wrapText=TRUE, horizontal="ALIGN_CENTER") 
csVar <- CellStyle(outwb) + Font(outwb, isBold=TRUE) + Alignment(wrapText=TRUE, horizontal="ALIGN_CENTER") 
csRatio <- CellStyle(outwb)+DataFormat("0.00") + Alignment(wrapText=TRUE, horizontal="ALIGN_CENTER") 
csPval <- CellStyle(outwb)+ DataFormat("#.###E+0") + Alignment(wrapText=TRUE, horizontal="ALIGN_CENTER") 
csAnnot <- CellStyle(outwb)+Alignment(wrapText=TRUE, horizontal="ALIGN_CENTER") 
csCols <- list("1"=csVar, "2"=csRatio, "3"=csPval, "4"=csAnnot) 

# populate data into workbook with basic styles
addDataFrame(wb_data,outsheet,col.names=T, row.names=F, startRow=1, startColumn=1, colStyle=csCols, colnamesStyle=csColNames, showNA=F, characterNA="")
setColumnWidth(outsheet,colIndex=4,colWidth=11)

# Style cells specifically according to their values
ratiorows=2:(nrow(wb_data)+1) 
for(each in ratiorows){
  ratiocell <- getCells(getRows(outsheet, rowIndex=each),colIndex=2,simplify=TRUE)
  pvalcell <- getCells(getRows(outsheet, rowIndex=each),colIndex=3,simplify=TRUE)
  ratio <- getCellValue(ratiocell[[1]])
  pval <-getCellValue(pvalcell[[1]])
  if( ratio >=1.5  && pval<=0.01){
    csCell <- CellStyle(outwb) + Fill(foregroundColor="yellow") + Font(outwb, isBold=TRUE)
  }else if(ratio <=1/1.5  && pval<=0.01){
    csCell <- CellStyle(outwb) + Fill(foregroundColor="cyan") + Font(outwb, isBold=TRUE)
  }else {
    csCell <- CellStyle(outwb) + Font(outwb, color="grey", isBold=T) 
  }
  setCellStyle(ratiocell[[1]], csCell)  
}

#write it out
saveWorkbook(outwb, file="my_examples.xlsx")
